@startuml user_account_state_diagram

title User Account State Diagram - LearnMate Platform
note top
  **System:** User status management for Student, Teacher, and Admin accounts
  **Key Field:** User.IsActive (boolean) + User.DeletedAt (nullable DateTime)
end note

[*] --> Creating: CreateUserAsync(\nNewUserRequestDto request)

note on the right of Creating
  **CREATING STATE**
  Trigger: Admin creates new user
  Actions:
    1. Email validated (unique check)
    2. Password hashed with BCrypt
    3. Create User entity with IsActive = true
    4. Create StudentProfile or TeacherProfile
    5. Persist to database
  Duration: Immediate transition
  Exit: → Active
end note

Creating --> Active: User.IsActive = true\n(Successfully Created)

Active --> Blocked: ChangeUserStatusAsync(\nuserid, isActive=false, reason)\n\nReasons:\n• Teacher Violation\n• Account Abuse\n• Policy Breach\n• Compliance Rejection\n• Payment Default

note on the right of Active
  **ACTIVE STATE**
  User.IsActive = true
  User.DeletedAt = null
  
  Capabilities:
    ✅ Can login to system
    ✅ Full access based on role
    ✅ Can access classes
    ✅ Can submit assignments
    ✅ Can make payments
    ✅ Can participate in sessions
  
  For TEACHER:
    ✅ Can create classes
    ✅ Can grade submissions
    ✅ Can receive payments
  
  For STUDENT:
    ✅ Can enroll in classes
    ✅ Can view materials
    ✅ Can submit assignments
  
  Duration: Unlimited (until blocked/deleted)
end note

Blocked --> Active: ChangeUserStatusAsync(\nuserId, isActive=true, unblockReason)\n\nReasons:\n• Appeal Approved\n• Temporary Block Expired\n• Verification Completed\n• Manual Admin Override

note on the left of Blocked
  **BLOCKED STATE**
  User.IsActive = false
  User.DeletedAt = null
  
  Restrictions:
    ❌ Cannot login
    ❌ Cannot access any features
    ❌ Session authentication fails
    ❌ Cannot perform any actions
  
  Data Preserved:
    ✓ All user data intact
    ✓ Classes and assignments preserved
    ✓ Payment history retained
  
  For TEACHER:
    ❌ Cannot create classes
    ❌ Cannot grade submissions
    ❌ Existing classes frozen
  
  For STUDENT:
    ❌ Cannot access enrolled classes
    ❌ Cannot submit assignments
    ❌ Cannot make payments
  
  Block Reason: Stored in database notes
  Duration: Until admin unblocks
end note

Active --> SoftDeleted: DeleteUserAsync(userId)\nuser.DeletedAt = DateTime.UtcNow()

Blocked --> SoftDeleted: DeleteUserAsync(userId)\nuser.DeletedAt = DateTime.UtcNow()

note on the right of SoftDeleted
  **SOFT DELETED STATE**
  User.IsActive = false (or true)
  User.DeletedAt ≠ null (timestamp set)
  
  Characteristics:
    • Record NOT physically removed
    • Hidden from user lists
    • Cannot login anymore
    • Cannot be restored via automatic process
    • Requires admin manual query
  
  Data:
    ✓ User record preserved
    ✓ All relations intact
    ✓ Payment history retained
    ✓ Assignment history retained
  
  Compliance:
    ✓ GDPR requirement (audit trail)
    ✓ Financial records maintained
    ✓ Class history preserved
    ✓ Payment dispute evidence
  
  SQL Query Pattern:
    WHERE deleted_at IS NULL  (normal users)
    WHERE deleted_at IS NOT NULL  (deleted users)
  
  Duration: Permanent (unless manually restored)
end note

SoftDeleted --> [*]: Account Fully Archived

note on the bottom of [*]
  **KEY IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS:**
  
  1. User Entity (BusinessObject/Models/Identity/User.cs):
     - public bool IsActive { get; set; } = true;
     - public DateTime? DeletedAt { get; set; }  // From SoftDeletableEntity base
  
  2. Service Method (BusinessLogicLayer/Services/UserManagementService.cs):
     - ChangeUserStatusAsync(long userId, bool isActive, string reason, string notes)
     - DeleteUserAsync(long userId)
  
  3. Database (PostgreSQL - users table):
     - Column: is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
     - Column: deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL
     - Column: updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ AUTO_UPDATE
  
  4. UI (LearnmateSolution/Components/Pages/Admin/Admin_UserManagement.razor):
     - Modals: Block, Unblock, Delete
     - Validations: Reason required, Name confirmation for delete
     - Filters: Show by role and status
end note

@enduml
